Linus, Luke, and Dan revisit the latest season of Scrapyard Wars and debate how much rule-bending actually happened. They argue over “permission” that may never have been granted, the infamous subwoofer, Shadow streaming, and whether certain builds should have even been allowed. The crew also looks back on past seasons, past disqualifications, and what rules need to change before the next competition.

Tesla has officially changed what “Full Self-Driving” means, downgrading it to “supervised” driver assistance after years of promising full autonomy. Linus and Luke discuss the decade-long gap between Tesla’s marketing and reality, Musk’s constant overpromises, and whether regulators or class actions will hold the company accountable. They also dive into the hype around Optimus and why the robot program looks like smoke and mirrors.

Luke recounts a brutal 30+ hour journey involving three cars, three trains, and three planes, with endless delays along the way, just to barely make it to the WAN Show on time. Linus jumps in with his own chaotic travel stories, from near-missed flights to paying $1,200 last-minute for a seat home. Linus and Luke discuss the misery (and occasional comedy) of travel gone wrong.
